<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="428" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,869,1137]" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">
DISTRIBUTION: Widespread species, recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[774,842,967,993]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[859,928,967,993]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[942,1089,967,993]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1149,1245,967,993]" country="Brazil" name="Roraima" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Roraima</collectingRegion>
States), 
<collectingCountry box="[1347,1432,967,993]" name="Bolivia" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,264,1003,1029]" name="Colombia" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[276,366,1003,1029]" name="Guyana" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[424,543,1003,1029]" name="Venezuela" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,869,1137]" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">
HABITAT RECORDS: Wide variety of habitats, including weeds on mud of drying pond, debris at edge of forest creek (
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, P. D." box="[229,385,1075,1101]" pageId="3" pageNumber="428" pagination="3 - 554" refId="ref5273" refString="Perkins, P. D. (1980) Aquatic beetles of the family Hydraenidae in the Western Hemisphere: classification, biogeography and inferred phylogeny (Insecta: Coleoptera). Quaestiones entomologicae, 16, 3 - 554." type="journal article" year="1980">Perkins 1980</bibRefCitation>
); ponds (
<bibRefCitation author="Benetti, C. J. &amp; Valladares, L. F. &amp; Delgado, J. A. &amp; Hamada, N." box="[493,715,1075,1101]" pageId="3" pageNumber="428" pagination="1" refId="ref4071" refString="Benetti, C. J., Valladares, L. F., Delgado, J. A. &amp; Hamada, N. (2021) Morphological remarks on Adelphydraena amazonica Perkins &amp; Ribera, 2020 and new records of two other Hydraenidae from Brazil (Coleoptera). Zootaxa, 4966 (1), 061 - 068. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4966.1.6" type="journal article" year="2021">
Benetti 
<emphasis box="[586,645,1075,1101]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
); small pools on sand bar, lake, river, pond, stream, vegetated backwater margins, lagoon, marshy area in river floodplain (
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, P. D." box="[828,981,1111,1137]" pageId="3" pageNumber="428" pagination="1 - 198" refId="ref5436" refString="Perkins, P. D. (2011) New records and description of fifty-four new species of aquatic beetles in the genus Hydraena Kugelann from South America (Coleoptera: Hydraenidae). Zootaxa, 3074 (1), 1 - 198. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3074.1.1" type="journal article" year="2011">Perkins 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
